<subSubSection pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[151,1436,1213,1957]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,324,1213,1238]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" reason="1">Redescription.</emphasis>
Forewings 2.2 times longer than wide, length: male 
<quantity box="[920,1055,1213,1237]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="3.9" metricValueMin="3.4" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" unit="mm" value="3.65" valueMax="3.9" valueMin="3.4">3.4–3.9 mm</quantity>
(mean = 3.6, n= 19), female 3.3– 4.0 mm (mean = 3.8, n= 13). Colour reddish brown above; stramineous underneath, but frons, subantennal processes, and margins of facial carinae also reddish brown; antennae and fore tarsi red; abdomen including genitalia bright red in male, in female (and in 
<specimenCount box="[565,667,1321,1345]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
specimen but not the 
<typeStatus box="[915,1015,1321,1345]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">holotype</typeStatus>
) abdominal tergites red, sternites and genitalia brown. Forewings and hindwings infuscated; veins and stridulation area of hindwings bright red. Rostrum slightly surpassing hindcoxae. Forewings with Sc+R fork just distad of basal third; Ms1 branched just distad of its basal quarter; a crossvein connecting bases of Ms1 and Cu1; a triangle at base of Ms1. Hindwings only about half as wide as forewings; stridulation area large. Male genitalia with pygofer narrow. Genital styles oval; proximal dorsal process short, slender; base of distal dorsal process slightly swollen, close to proximal process. Aedeagus short; apical part with two flat, terminal lobes, twisted by about 45°.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
